                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JOHN CROFT</hi>
                  </persName> and <persName id="def2-1256a-18400406" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def2-1256a-18400406" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-1256a-18400406" type="surname" value="CROFT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-1256a-18400406" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">MARY CROFT</hi>
                  </persName> were indicted for<rs id="t18400406-1256a-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18400406-1256a-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18400406-1256a-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp> stealing, on the <rs id="t18400406-cd-214" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18400406-1256a-offence-1 t18400406-cd-214"></join>27th of March</rs>, 1 copper-lid, value 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., the goods, of <persName id="t18400406-name-1304" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1304" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1304" type="surname" value="NICHOLSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1304" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18400406-1256a-offence-1 t18400406-name-1304"></join>James Ni<lb></lb>cholson</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400406-name-1305" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1305" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1305" type="surname" value="NICHOLSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1305" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES NICHOLSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I keep the sutling-house at St. James's-palace. On the 27th of March the prisoners came to my house together, about four o'clock in the afternoon—the man asked for half-a-pint of beer—they went into the tap-room, and sat together—I had seen this copper-lid safe that day between eleven and twelve o'clock—I had occasion to send the boy out while they were in the tap-room, and while he was away the man came to the bar, and called for half-a-pint of beer—while I was serving, the woman passed me, and I saw the copper-lid projecting from under her cloak—the man stepped inside the tap-room, and then he followed her.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. CLARKSON</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Were there any people in the tap-room? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Not that tap-room—there was in another—I have not found the copper-lid.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Why did you not stop her? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> It is a usual thing for mechanics to come and eat their dinners at my house, and I thought it might be her property—all I know is I saw something like a copper-lid under her cloak.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400406-name-1306" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1306" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1306" type="surname" value="GALLIMORE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1306" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY GALLIMORE</persName>
                  </hi>. On the 27th of March I left the copper-lid safe a little after four o'clock—I came back in about five minutes, and then the party and the lid were gone.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Were there oyster people and other people in the tap-room? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—there were no soldiers in the other tap-room.</p>
               <p>
